{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0cf4df2f-c784-4513-884d-d68f5674fc07","content":"`SafeAreaEdges` isn't a standard .NET MAUI property — you're likely thinking of the **iOS-specific** `UseSafeArea` setting. And on Android, you need to explicitly opt into **edge-to-edge** rendering. Here's what to do:\n\n### XAML — ContentPage\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n             ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"\n             Padding=\"0\"\n             NavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\">\n\n    <Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n           Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n           VerticalOptions=\"Fill\"\n           HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### Android — edge-to-edge (MainActivity.cs)\n\n```csharp\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n    if (Window is not null)\n    {\n        Window.SetStatusBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n        Window.SetNavigationBarColor(Android.Graphics.Color.Transparent);\n\n        // Extend layout behind system bars\n        WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nYou'll need `using AndroidX.Core.View;` for `WindowCompat`.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Platform | What was missing |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| **iOS** | `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` (not `SafeAreaEdges`) |\n| **Android** | `WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window, false)` + transparent system bars |\n| **Both** | `Padding=\"0\"` on the page, hide the nav bar |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"787e77fb-fd24-432a-8cbe-075535db0974","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is working on a .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10 and wants an image to go edge-to-edge behind the status bar and navigation bar. They've tried setting `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage but still see padding.\n\nThis is a common .NET MAUI question. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. **`IgnoreSafeArea`** - In .NET MAUI, individual views need to opt out of safe area insets. Setting `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the page may not be sufficient on its own.\n\n2. On **iOS**, the safe area insets push content away from the status bar and home indicator. \n\nFor iOS specifically, I need to set `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on the ContentPage to disable safe area handling. On Android, edge-to-edge rendering requires opting in through platform-specific configuration, and in .NET 9+, Android 15 actually enforces this by default, so the approach depends on the target Android version. For iOS, I need to use the platform-specific namespace and set `UseSafeArea=\"False\"` on the page. On Android, the solution involves configuring edge-to-edge display by making the system bars transparent and disabling the default window insets behavior through platform code. The image itself should then extend behind these system UI elements. For Android, I need to configure the app to extend behind system bars by setting up the window in the platform-specific code and ensuring the page has no padding to achieve the edge-to-edge effect.","outputTokens":1467},"id":"dd826183-d483-4c95-96b7-01fbced26e07","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:53:34.119Z","parentId":"a41f0c43-f6c9-4115-9753-c70272d40ca8"}
